caption: Fast service

Hefty helpings for sandwiches. Fresh carved meat, instead of processed/packed deli meat.  At most places, you ask for extra, but here, sometimes I would ask for less than what they provide.  Of course the fresh bread is what matters for a sandwich.  Breakfast croissants are great too.
Always fresh and good
I used to work near this cafe over 10 years ago.  They are under new management but still have good food.  A bit expensive but good.
Nice people. Good food but limited selections because of COVID.
Great sandwiches and soups

I work nearby so this is a bit of a treat for me. The meat portions are generous and they carve the meat while putting the sandwiches together for you. There is some struggle with some employees having strong accents but they're rather hospitable. I like coming here from time to time with my coworkers. Pros: Food is great quality, polite employees, not too far away from L'Enfant Plaza station. Cons: You gotta get here early if you want to grab a bite and go, space is limited--don't expect that you can sit alone if you're at one of the bigger tables.
Nice little deli with top quality sandwiches and soups
They are liberal when putting your sandwich together and don't skimp on the ingredients.
(Translated by Google) Very delicious breakfasts and very friendly attention  (Original) Unos desayunos riquisimos y la atencion muy amable
Turkey, ham and roast beef cooked fresh each morning. Sandwiches are great
Good sandwich shop with a large variety of sandwiches for lunch. Will definitely return

I like their meat portions on our meal. They are generally generous with it. The location is great from my workplace. The guy at the registrar is generally cool and friendly. There's long line sometimes during the peak lunch hours but that's normal for any place. The employees sometimes could be difficult to understand due to the language barrier but overall a great Cafe for brunch and lunch.
Fresh turkey
Worth the walk. Best fresh sandwiches around that area.
It's near wurk. But too expensive for something that should be quick.
Great spot for breakfast on the run. The owner takes pride in her establishment and is a kind and friendly person.
Had the BLT  it was AWESOME.........
Food is always amazing!!!!!
A quick place to get good food
Amazing service! Always service with a smile! Staff is always friendly, polite and patient. We had breakfast here a few times and the food was delicious and priced just right!!
Great hit Turkey sandwich. I have never gone wrong here.

Atrium cafe is a lovely dining place. I ordered the egg and cheese sandwich on whole wheat and bagel with veggie cream cheese, which were all delicious for breakfast and lunch. The egg sandwich was huge. It could feed 2 people. I would recommend this cafe.
Jay that works the line is one of the most talented and organized chefs I have seen.
This is not your average office sandwich shop, they make your sandwich in front of you, cutting the meat right off of the bone.
Love the pastrami sub. Real deli meats
Best sandwiches around! Love the freshly cooked ham and turkey.
Great sandwhiches with "real" not provessed deli meat
Long line worth the fresh meal!
Great sandwiches
Good food great service
Food very good

It's more expensive than Rise and Shine, but overall food (sandwiches) is better. They also have a cold/hot bars plus basic set of beverages. Please note that while cafe is open until 3.45 P.M., the grill is closing before, around 2.45 or so. Interesting, that the address is 400 Virginia Avenue SW, but it has entrance from the School street, almost on the corner of the School and 4th St SW.
Great value for your $. I ordered the turkey wrap. Deli will make anything to order for you.
Excellent Cafe!!

Great food and options in terms of salads and other snacks. Enjoyable atmosphere and always polite staff. Lines can be long and the grill is usually shut off around an hour before they close, so plan ahead if you want to enjoy one of the hot sandwiches.

Decent sandwich place, made to order from freshly sliced meat.  Also have some other things on the menu like Korean BBQ Wrap.  Drinks are either from the refrigerator or fountain.  Reasonably priced, first floor of an office building.

This used to be a very nice place.  Now they have changed staff and the service has slipped.  They are processing food like a service line and not a food store.  I told them my order and no one asked what I wanted on my sandwich.  They proceeded to fix it their way without my input. When I said something, I was given nasty looks and then the sandwich started falling apart because the server was angry.  I did not want the sandwich any more.  I have been coming to this place for years and was very disappointed.  They are not cheap and need to care more about serving people than collecting money.
Fresh carved meats and friendly service- a solid lunch choice
Good food at a price typical of the area. Not flashy, but satisfying.
Don't tell anybody but this is the best sandwich shop near the mall.  Fresh baked bread and shaved meats on every sandwich.  Haven't had anything other than delicious everytime I'm here.
average food, waay over priced
Great sandwiches

Wouldn't accept my Discover card unless I met their "minimum".  I refused to up my purchase, therefore the sandwich was thrown away by the cashier......its unfortunate this business had to eat their food cost just because they did not want to pay merchant transaction fees..........WILL NEVER RETURN
Great place, wonderful staff, excellent food and always clean and food is fresh. Great place for breakfast or lunch.
Fresh cut meats on a variety of different breads! A little overpriced, but so is everything in DC.
Breakfast bagel was chewey and tasteless.  I scooped out the egg and cheese and threw away the bagel.  Toasting or butter didn't help it any.  Go for the sourdough bread, that's good.
Beautiful food and ambience
If you want a sandwich in the area. They are the best. Sure you will pay a little more than Subway but you will get a whole lot more.
Federal workers lunch time sandwiches. That is all.
My favorite place to grab a sandwich in the l'enfant area. The roast beef is one of the best options. It can get a little crowded at noon on a weekday but the line moves fast.

Always Rude here - and super over priced. When you ask for something its like you're begging them and they say sorry - its not lunch time. Or even worse they will say no its still breakfast. What's the problem if I'm paying for your bland food in the first place?  The Owners are not nice. Therefore their employees are not happy and are mean too.  Horrible customer service.  They don't even greet you when you walk in - its just another customer another dollar.  Treat people with respect - there are plenty of other places that will gladly take my money.  Last Resort - if you're starving.

This is a great Korean owned deli they serve a lot of American Sandwiches that are cut from real meat and not processed meat. This is unusual and very welcomed into the modern culinary where quality is more welcomed than processed. Staff is friendly and food comes out fast.
Good food. Turkey and ham are freshly baked and used in the sandwiches. Food is good quality.
Generously stack meat on sandwiches. The food is not great but its an ok place for a quick lunch
Great large sandwiches, large enough to share. Enjoy the freshly cut Roast Beef and Turkey. They move fast, but there can be some waiting on line.
Prices are fair
Rude staff. I wanted to use my card but they made me buy more food so I can use my card. And show attitude. Food is k.
Great spot for breakfast and lunch. Line can get long between noon and 1pm.
Tuna melt is awesome
Fresh food every single time and hot muffins straight out oven are to die for.
Excellent sandwiches.
I come her for lunch everytime I'm working in DC. Great selection of fresh made sandwiches and wraps at reasonable prices.
Excellent sandwiches made to order.
Best sandwiches in dc. Hands down
Great hand carved sandwiches.
Good food and coffee.
Good BLT, friendly service.
Services was great. Went for lunch and love the grill sandwich... defiantly will return.. A must go!!!
Beautiful place and great customer service
Service was great!
lots of menu to choose~ tasty & delicious! clean & bright & space! so nice place!
A must try restaurant. In particular, we strongly recommend bulgogi wrap.
The sandwich is delicious The ingredients are fresh The store is very clean
Perfect place for tourists. Good foods, clean and kind place.
Fresh cuts and quick line make this a nice lunch option

Calling it a cafe is a long jump ... small coffee, soup, and sandwich shop supporting the office building where it is located; on the first floor. Don't believe it is open in the evening and/or weekends. Only public parking.
Very tasty sandwiches. Pretty good pre-made salad bowls, too.

The food is good but the customer service is atrocious! Improve your customer service and be courteous to your clients. Rule No. 1. I was told to stand back in the sandwich line when all I was getting was a salad.
I believe that the Atrium Cafe offers the best lunch in the immediate area.  They carve their own meats for sandwiches that are made to order and yummy!
Omelettes are delicious and meat in sandwiches is generous!
They have the best sandwiches
Good for a quick bite.
Ok food a bit rude at the counter but it was early more expensive than most in the area
Quick service and friendly staff. Just be sure to have cash if your order is < $5.
Great place
Standard cafe fare. great spot for breakfast or lunch if you work in the area.
Nice spot for coffee or lunch
Hand carved deli that's good for lunch. Plenty of white and red meat options but limited vegetarian options.
Great service and fresh food that isn't expensive for DC.

Great place.  I love their sandwiches but my favorite is their fresh carrot and orange juices.  Also very friendly staff. Strongly recommended if you come around here. Very business oriented for office people.

Customer Service needs to be a consistent conversation in this place.  I went to order a breakfast sandwich and I asked the sandwich maker how my food would be prepared she said "relax" with an attitude and then I tried to ask again to get her to provide a response at that time she just ignored me and i decided to leave.  Before leaving I politely told her that she could scratch my order.  Although the food is good the customer service needs to be addressed.  if some ask a question about an order they are placing it should be met with hesitation or attitude.  After all it's food I have to eat not the preparer.

I know this is a bold statement but I had the best roast beef sandwhich I hav3 ever had. Roast beef done rare fresh cut infront of you. I had min on sourdough. I will be going back for more. Only thing missing from my meal wiuld be fried Wisconsin cheese curds.

One of the better in and out sandwich places in Farragut area. Love coming here for the occasional breakfast sandwich (nice selection of fresh bagels!). Line moves quickly. Friendly service. Prices reflect the business district (real estate). Can do my Post Office tasks which is located on the same area. It's below ground, come into the building and go down the escalators 😊
(Translated by Google) This place is crap especially bosses.  (Original) Este lugar es una mierda especialmente los jefes.
Absolutely the best place for lunch sandwiches.  Freshly carved meat and lots of veggie options.  Love this place!
Yummy food, reasonably priced, clean environment. A great spot for lunch.

I came here yesterday with a friend for lunch. The line moved quickly, the meat is hand-carve to order and there were a lot of options for bread and sandwich toppings. The freshly-carved turkey sandwich was delicious. The meat was still a little warm from being in the oven...mmm! I'll be back.

I used to work in the same building as this location and the sandwiches rock. As mentioned previously, they slice the meat right in front of you: turkey, ham, chicken. All sandwiches are made to order with a fairly large selection of bread, cheese, and condiments. Okay place to sit and eat lunch. My project team and I would go down and eat there for lunch. Their breakfast service is usually really awesome too. Good egg sandwiches.  I will note that the area around the building is not that great. It literally is on the other side of the train tracks. Therefore, if you were planning on coming here as a tourist, I'd suggest to stay away.
